{{Main|Logarithmic timeline}}
This timeline shows the whole [[history of the universe]], the [[Earth]], and [[Human|mankind]] in one table. Each row is defined in ''years ago'', that is, [[year]]s before the present [[calendar date|date]], with the earliest times at the top of the chart. In each table cell on the right, references to events or notable people are given, more or less in chronological order within the cell.
Each row corresponds to a change in log(time before present) of about 0.1 (using log base 10). The dividing points are taken from the R′′20 [[Renard numbers]].
The table is divided into sections with subtitles. Note that each such section contains about 68% of all the time from the beginning of the section until now.
