0-neanderthals-were-ancient-mariners/}}</ref> Signs of ''Homo'' in California.<!--128 ka BC--><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Steven Holen et al.|title=A 130,000-year-old archaeological site in southern California, USA|journal=Nature|date=Apr 2017|doi=10.1038/nature22065|pmid=28447646|volume=544|issue=7651|pages=479–483|bibcode=2017Natur.544..479H}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Colin Barras|title=Neanderthals first to reach America?|journal=New Scientist|date=May 6, 2017|url=https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg23431241-600-first-americans-may-have-been-neanderthals-130000-years-ago}}</ref> [[Neanderthal]]s make ornaments from eagle claws.<!--128 ka BC--><ref>{{cite journal|author1=D. Radovčić ''et al.''|title=Evidence for Neandertal Jewelry: Modified White-Tailed Eagle Claws at Krapina|journal=[[PLOS ONE]]|date=Mar 11, 2016|doi=10.1371/journal.pone.0119802|volume=10|issue=3|page=e0119802|pmid=25760648|pmc=4356571|bibcode=2015PLoSO..1019802R}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Neanderthal chic|journal=New Scientist|date=Aug 13, 2016|url=https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg23130864-600}}</ref> Temperatures generally higher than today during the [[Eemian]] interglacial. [[Late Eemian Aridity Pulse]].<!--116 ka BC--><ref>{{cite journal|author1=F. Sirocko ''et al.''|title=A late Eemian aridity pulse in central Europe during the last glacial inception|journal=Nature|date=Aug 11, 2005|doi=10.1038/nature03905|volume=436|issue=7052|pages=833–836|pmid=16094365|bibcode=2005Natur.436..833S}}</ref> Tools used at [[Talepu]] site in [[Sulawesi]].<!--At latest 116 ka BC--><ref>{{cite journal|author1=Gerrit van den Bergh|author2=''et al.''|title=Earliest hominin occupation of Sulawesi, Indonesia|journal=Nature|date=Jan 2016|doi=10.1038/nature16448|volume=529|issue=7585|pages=208–211|pmid=26762458|bibcode=2016Natur.529..208V|url=http://ro.uow.edu.au/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=4486&context=smhpapers}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Tool find hints Java Man and hobbit had early human n