/ref> (seemingly the divisional MP company of the [[24th Infantry Division (United States)|24th Infantry Division]]) worked with other [[United Nations Command]] [[military police]] in Yong Ju Gol to keep [[Law and order (politics)|law and order]] in the area. In 1966, a [[museum]] dedicated to the [[2nd Infantry Division (United States)|2nd Infantry Division]] was opened near Yong Ju Gol, having been relocated there from [[Fort Benning]], [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]], but the museum was moved to [[Camp Casey, South Korea|Camp Casey]] five years later.<ref>{{Cite book|pages=95–96|title=Guide to U.S. Army Museums|author=R. Cody Phillips|publisher=Diane Publishing|year=1992|isbn=0788146718}}</ref> In 1980, American soldier Freddie Grant attacked another American soldier with a [[straight razor]] outside a Yong Ju Gol [[nightclub]] and was subsequently imprisoned in the [[United States Disciplinary Barracks]].<ref>{{Cite news|work=[[The State (newspaper)|The State]] |title=Richland County kidnapping suspect booted from military after cutting, kidnapping fellow soldiers |date=November 9, 2012 |author=Noelle Phillips |url=http://www.thestate.com/2012/11/09/2512799/sc-kidnapping-suspect-booted-from.html |accessdate=June 22, 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121213014604/http://www.thestate.com/2012/11/09/2512799/sc-kidnapping-suspect-booted-from.html |archivedate=December 13, 2012 }}</ref> Although it is illegal to engage in [[prostitution in South Korea]], women continue to engage in [[sex work]] in Yong Ju Gol through [[massage parlor]]s, [[Karaoke#Karaoke in South Korea|karaoke bars]], and kissing rooms.<ref>{{Cite journal|journal=Groove Korea|title='Girls Are Not For Sale'|author=Dylan Goldby|author2=Daniel Sanchez |author3=Matthew Lamers |date=March 20, 2012|url=http://groovekorea.com/article/girls-are-not-sale|accessdate=April 13, 2013}}</ref> In 2006, South Korea's [[Ministry of Gender Equality and Family|Minister of Gender Equality and Family]], Jang Ha-jin, called Yong Ju Gol "the heart of prostitution" in Korea.<ref>{{Cite news|work=[[JoongAng Ilbo#Korea JoongAng Daily|Korea JoongAng Daily]]|title=Aide runs up white flag in red-light controversy|date=December 27, 2006|author=Moon Kyung-ran|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joinsmsn.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=2863878|accessdate=June 22, 2013}}</ref> A popular ''[[manhwa]]'' called ''Yongjugol Blues'' glamorizes the [[prostitution]] in the area.<ref>{{Cite news|work=[[The Korea Times]]|title=Korea's dirty secret|author=Mike Long|date=February 24, 2012|url=http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/opinon/2013/05/161_105640.html|accessdate=June 22, 2013}}</ref>
